---
source: crates/normalize/tests/cli_snapshots.rs
expression: "snapshot_help(&[\"analyze\", \"trace\"])"
---
Analyze codebase (health, complexity, security, duplicates, docs)

Usage: normalize analyze [OPTIONS] [target]

Arguments:
  [target]  Target file or directory

Options:
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
  -r, --root <root>                Root directory (defaults to current directory)
      --exclude <exclude>          Exclude paths matching pattern
      --only <only>                Include only paths matching pattern
  -l, --limit <limit>              Maximum number of large files to include in output (0 = no limit, default 10)
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version

Commands:
  health             Run health analysis (file counts, complexity stats, large file warnings)
  all                Run all analysis passes
  summary            Auto-generated single-page codebase overview

Code quality:
  complexity-trend   Show how average cyclomatic complexity has changed over git history.
  length             Find the longest functions in the codebase, ranked by line count.
  length-trend       Show how average function length has changed over git history.
  node-types         List all node types and field names for a tree-sitter grammar.

Module structure:
  density-trend      Show how information density has changed over git history.

Repository:
  docs               Measure documentation coverage: which public symbols lack doc comments.

Graph analysis:
  architecture       Analyze architectural structure: coupling, dependency cycles, and hub modules.

Git history:
  coupling-clusters  Find clusters of files that change together in git history (connected components).
  activity           Show commit activity across multiple repositories over time windows.
  repo-coupling      Detect temporal coupling between repositories: pairs that receive commits together.
  cross-repo-health  Rank repositories by composite tech-debt score (churn × complexity × coupling).
  trend              Track multiple health metrics (complexity, length, test ratio, density) over git history.

Testing:
  test-gaps          Identify public functions that lack test coverage, ranked by risk score.
  test-ratio-trend   Show how the test-to-code ratio has changed over git history.

Security:
  security           Scan the codebase for security issues (hardcoded secrets, unsafe patterns).

Diff:
  skeleton-diff      Show structural (skeleton) changes between a base ref and HEAD.
